In [20]:
centre = []
for c in cnts:
# finding the center of the contour
    
    M = cv2.moments(c)
    if M["m00"] != 0:
        cX = int(M["m10"] / M["m00"])
        cY = int(M["m01"] / M["m00"])
    else:
        cX, cY = 0, 0
    
    centre.append(cY)

    cv2.drawContours(sep_coin, [c], -1, (0, 255, 0), 2)
    cv2.circle(sep_coin, (cX, cY), 30, (0, 0, 255), -1)
    cv2.putText(sep_coin, "center", (cX - 20, cY - 20),
        cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 10, (255, 255, 255), 20)
